Here's some information about how recipes are structured: @backend/docs/recipes.md 

You can verify the quality of the code by running `go run github.com/dinnerdonebetter/backend/cmd/playground`

I need you to create a new recipe file with a text recipe that I will provide. Please separate every recipe into a step involving a single valid preparation, with its requisite ingredients/vessels/instruments per step. Be precise, if not fickle: If an instruction says "pat dry the steak and then season it," that's two steps: one to dry, and one to season. If there's an instruction that prepares a cooking vessel, i.e. lining a baking sheet with aluminum foil, that is its own step. If you encounter a preparation or ingredient that you don't already have, add it to the already-existing lists of ingredients in the enumerations file here: @backend/internal/domain/mealplanning/bootstrap/enumerations.go

If a recipe step has the word "until" in it, it probably needs a recipe step completion condition.

If the recipe presents you with any ahead-of-time prep steps, please use them to create RecipePrepTasks associated with the recipe.

If you feel uncertain about anything, please feel free to ask clarifying questions.

The recipe is titled "TITLE", it's source is LINK:

```
<copied_recipe>
```



